name: BMW
historical_introduction: BMW is a German manufacturer of motorcycles, engines, and cars. BMW is known for its high-quality motorcycles and cars. BMW motorcycles are popular among riders who want a high-quality, reliable, and high-performance motorcycle.

name: Ducati
historical_introduction: Ducati is an Italian manufacturer of motorcycles. Ducati is known for its high-performance motorcycles. Ducati started as a radio manufacturer in 1926, and it started making motorcycles in 1946.

name: Harley-Davidson
historical_introduction: Harley-Davidson is an American manufacturer of motorcycles. Harley-Davidson is known for its cruiser motorcycles. Harley-Davidson motorcycles are known for their style, sound, and heritage.

name: Honda
historical_introduction: Honda is a Japanese manufacturer of motorcycles, engines, and cars.

name: Kawasaki
historical_introduction: Kawasaki is a Japanese manufacturer of motorcycles, engines, and cars. Kawasaki is a big japanese conglomerate, and it started making motorcycles in 1963.

name: KTM
historical_introduction: KTM is an Austrian manufacturer of motorcycles. KTM started as a metalworking shop in 1934, and it started making motorcycles in 1953.

name: Suzuki
historical_introduction: Suzuki is a Japanese manufacturer of motorcycles, engines, and cars. Suzuki started as a loom manufacturer in 1909, and it started making motorcycles in 1952.

name: Triumph
historical_introduction: Triumph is a British manufacturer of motorcycles.

name: Yamaha
historical_introduction: Yamaha is a Japanese manufacturer of musical instruments, motorcycles, engines, and cars. Yamaha started as a musical instrument manufacturer in 1887, and it started making motorcycles in 1955.
